.joins.com/html/136/NB11615136.html|title=\uc81c54\ud68c \ubc31\uc0c1\uc608\uc220\ub300\uc0c1, TV\u00b7\uc601\ud654 \uac01 \ubd80\ubb38\ubcc4 \uc218\uc0c1 \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc790 \uacf5\uac1c|date=April 6, 2018|website=JTBC|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2018 SBS Entertainment Awards|12th]] [[SBS Entertainment Awards]]\n|Excellence Award in Show/Talk Category\n|''[[My Little Old Boy]]''<br />''{{illm|The Fan (South Korean TV series)|lt=The Fan|ko|\ub354 \ud32c}}''<br />''[[Reckless but Happy]]''\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20181229/93483966/1|title=[\uc885\ud569] 'SBS \uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1' \uc774\uc2b9\uae30 \ub300\uc0c1\u2026\uae40\uc885\uad6d\u2661\ud64d\uc9c4\uc601 \ubca0\uc2a4\ud2b8\ucee4\ud50c\uc0c1|website=sports.donga.com|language=ko|access-date=2018-12-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mosen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111056472|title='\ubc18\uc804\uc758 \ub300\uc0c1' \ubc1b\uc740 \ubc30\uc6b0..\uc62c\ud574\uc758 \ud504\ub85c\uadf8\ub7a8 '\ubbf8\uc6b0\uc0c8'(\uc885\ud569)[2018 SBS\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1]|last=OSEN|date=2018-12-29|website=mosen.mt.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2018-12-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[2018 MBC Entertainment Awards|18th]] [[MBC Entertainment Awards]]\n|Excellence Award, Music/Talk Category \u2013 Male\n|rowspan=2|{{illm|Section TV|ko|\uc139\uc158TV \uc5f0\uc608\ud1b5\uc2e0}}<br />{{illm|Cafeteria (South Korean TV series)|lt=Cafeteria|ko|\uad6c\ub0b4\uc2dd\ub2f9 - \ub0a8\uc758 \ud68c\uc0ac \uc720\ub791\uae30}}\n|{{nom}}\n|rowspan=2|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1S8NXY0LF5/GL0101|title=[MBC \uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1] \uc774\uc601\uc790, KBS \uc774\uc5b4 MBC \ub300\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1\u2026\uc5ec\uc131 \ucd5c\ucd08 2\uad00\uc655|date=2018-12-30|website=\uc11c\uc6b8\uacbd\uc81c|language=ko|access-date=2018-12-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news20.busan.com/controller/newsController.jsp?newsId=20181230000003|title=[MBC\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1] \ub300\uc0c1 \uc774\uc601\uc790, \uc1a1\uc131\ud638\uc640 \ub728\uac70\uc6b4 \ud3ec\uc639 '\uc5ed\ub300 \ucd5c\ucd08 \u5973 2\uad00\uc655'|last=\uae30\uc790|first=\ub514\uc9c0\ud138\ubcf8\ubd8013|website=\ubd80\uc0b0\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2018-12-31}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Entertainer Award - Music & Talk\n|{{won}}\n|-\n!2019\n|[[2019 SBS Entertainment Awards|13th]] [[SBS Entertainment Awards]]\n|Best Couple Award <small>with [[Tak Jae-hoon]]</small>\n|[[My Little Old Boy]]\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvreport.co.kr/2025351|title='SBS\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1' \uc720\uc7ac\uc11d, \ub300\uc0c1+'\ub7f0\ub2dd\ub9e8' 6\uad00\uc655 \uc2f9\uc4f8\uc774\u2026\ubc31\uc885\uc6d0 \uacf5\ub85c\uc0c1[\uc885\ud569]|website=TV\ub9ac\ud3ec\ud2b8|access-date=2019-12-29}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{The Genius (TV series)}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Sang-min}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television personalities]]\n[[Category:South Korean dance musicians]]\n[[Category:South Korean record producers]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n[[Category:Weekly Idol members]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n\n\n{{SouthKorea-singer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Expand Korean|\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc (\uac00\uc218)|date=September 2018}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Lee Sang-min\n| image         = \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \uad11\uace0\ucd2c\uc601 \ud604\uc7a5 21s.jpg\n| alt           = Lee Sang-min in 2017\n| caption       = Lee Sang-min in 2017\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1973|2|3}}\n| birth_place   = [[Yeongdeungpo District]], [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place   =\n| nationality   =\n| other_names   =\n| occupation    = {{hlist|Singer|[[songwriter]]|record producer|television host}}\n| known_for     =\n| notable_works =\n| spouse        = {{marriage|[[Lee Hye-young (actress, born 1971)|Lee Hye-young]]|2004|2005}}\n| module        = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]|[[dance music|dance]]}}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| label            = Dmost Entertainment\n| associated_acts  = [[Roo'ra]]\n| years_active     = 1994\u2013present\n| module2          = {{Infobox Korean name | child = yes\n| hangul = {{linktext|\uc774|\uc0c1|\ubbfc}}\n| hanja  = {{linktext|\u674e|\u5c19|\u654f}}\n| rr     = I Sangmin\n| mr     = I Sangmin\n}}}}}}\n\n'''Lee Sang-min''' ({{Korean|\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc|\u674e\u5c19\u654f|rr=|mr=}}; born February 3, 1973)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/List/3/70030000000001/19980419/7338724/1|title=[\ud734\uc9c0\ud1b5] \uac15\ub0a8\uc77c\ub300\uc11c \uc720\uba85\uc778 \uc787\ub2e8 \uc218\ub09c|date=April 19, 1998|website=Dong-a Ilbo|language=ko|access-date=January 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.yeongnam.com/mnews/newsview.do?mode=newsView&newskey=20160607.990010847001185|title=\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \uc2e4\uc81c \ub098\uc774\ub294? \uae40\uc138\uc544 \uc0ac\uac74\uc740 \uc5b4\ub5bb\uac8c \uc9c4\ud589\ub418\uace0 \uc788\ub098? '\ud48d\ubb38\uc1fc'\uac00 \uc804\ud55c \uc5f0\uc608\uacc4 \uc774\uc288\ub294?|date=June 7, 2016|website=Yeongnam Ilbo|language=ko|access-date=January 24, 2019}}</ref> is a South Korean singer, songwriter, [[record producer]] and television personality. He is a former member of the hip hop and dance group [[Roo'ra]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201812311350558010|title='SBS \uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1' \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \"\uc77c\uc740 \uc81c\uc791\uc9c4\uc774 \ud558\ub294\ub370\u2025\uc8c4\uc1a1\ud558\uace0 \uac10\uc0ac\"|date=December 31, 2018|website=Newsen|language=ko|access-date=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n{{expand section|date=April 2018}}\n{{main|Roo'ra}}\nLee debuted with mix group ''[[Roo'ra]]'' in 1993 and hit the top with popular song ''[[Angel Without The Wing]]'' and ''[[Three!Four!]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kim |first=Min-ji |title=\ucd5c\uace0\uc758 \uadf8\ub8f9\uc5d0\uc11c \ube44\uc6b4\uc758 \uadf8\ub8f9\uc73c\ub85c - \ub8f0\ub77c\" |url=https://m.post.naver.com/viewer/postView.nhn?volumeNo=13102209&memberNo=2301197 |date=February 17, 2018 |language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn late 90's and early 00's, Lee was the most success producer along with ''[[Yang Hyun-suk]]''.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} He produced many hit group like ''[[Country Kko Kko]]'', ''[[Chakra (group)|Chakra]]'', and ''[[Sharp (South Korean band)|S#arp]]'' at his company Sangmind.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} Lee is also the one who scouted popular actress ''[[Jung Ryeo-won]]'' of ''[[Chakra (group)|Chakra]]'' and ''[[Hwangbo]]'' and ''[[Tak Jae-hoon]]'' of ''[[Country Kko Kko]]''.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\nOn March 27, 2018, [[MBC Every1]] announced that Lee would be joining the cast of [[Weekly Idol]] as a host, following a revamp to the series.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lee|first1=Seung-rok|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd] '\uc8fc\uac04\uc544' \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfcX\uae40\uc2e0\uc601X\uc720\uc138\uc724, 3MC \ud655\uc815\u2026\uc815\ud615\ub3c8\u00b7\ub370\ud504\ucf58 \uc774\ubc88\uc8fc \ub9c9\ubc29|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201803270938444732&ext=na|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=MyDaily|date=March 29, 2018|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Hong|first1=Seung-han|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc, '\uc8fc\uac04\uc544\uc774\ub3cc' \ud569\ub958 \ud655\uc815\u2026\uc720\uc138\uc724X\uae40\uc2e0\uc601 3MC \uccb4\uc81c|url=http://www.sportsseoul.com/news/read/616051|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Sports Seoul|date=March 27, 2018|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\nOn April 11, 2018, [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] announces that Lee is going to joined the upcoming music TV program ''[[The Call (South Korean TV series)|The Call]]'' as a host.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kim |first=Min-ji |title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc5e0\ub137 \uce21 \"\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc\u00b7\uc720\uc138\uc724, '\ub354 \ucf5c' MC \ubc1c\ud0c1\u2026 '\ucf00\ubbf8' \uae30\ub300\" |url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3286159 |accessdate=June 4, 2018 |work=News 1 |date=April 10, 2018 |language=ko}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn 1995, Lee, who was a member of Roo'ra at the time, attempted suicide following allegations that one of their songs plagiarized Ninja's debut song Omatsuri.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bae|first1=Ji-sook|title=Hyo-ri's plagiarism scandal snowballs|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2010/06/117_68217.html|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=The Korean Times|date=June 24, 2010}}</ref>\n\nOn June 19, 2004, Lee married actress and singer [[Lee Hye-young (actress, born 1971)|Lee Hye-young]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Yoo|first1=Sang-woo|title=\uac00\uc218 \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc-\uc774\ud61c\uc601 \ucee4\ud50c \uacb0\ud63c|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0000066756|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Newsis|publisher=Naver|date=June 20, 2004|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kim|first=Tae-geun|title=\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc-\uc774\ud61c\uc601 \ubc31\ub144\uac00\uc57d...\uc1a1\uc724\uc544 \ub4f1 \ud558\uac1d1500\uc5ec\uba85 \ucc38\uc11d|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0000004256|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Sports Chosun|publisher=Naver|date=June 20, 2004|language=Korean}}</ref> whom he met in the U.S. in 1996 and dated for seven years.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kang|first=Seung-hoon|title=\uc774\ud61c\uc601-\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \uc804\uaca9 \uc774\ud63c, \uacb0\ud63c 1\ub1442\uac1c\uc6d4\ub9cc\uc5d0 \ud30c\uacbd|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=117&aid=0000019223|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=MyDaily|date=August 9, 2005|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=7\ub144 \uc5f4\uc560 \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc - \uc774\ud61c\uc601 \uacb0\ud63c|url=http://news.khan.co.kr/kh_news/khan_art_view.html?artid=200406201852501&code=100203|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=The Kyunghyang Shinmun|date=June 20, 2004|language=Korean}}</ref> However, on August 8, 2005, the couple divorced, stating personality differences.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \uc774\ud61c\uc601 \uacb0\ud63c 1\ub144 2\uac1c\uc6d4 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \uc774\ud63c|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=001&aid=0001071244|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Yonhap News|publisher=Naver|date=August 10, 2005|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kim|first1=So-ra|title=\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc-\uc774\ud61c\uc601 \ucee4\ud50c \uacb0\ud63c 1\ub144\ub9cc\uc5d0 '\ud30c\uacbd'|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0000009236|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Sports Chosun|publisher=Naver|date=August 10, 2005|language=Korean}}</ref> In August 2006, Lee was sued by his ex-wife for fraud charges and taking about 2.2 billion won prior to their marriage and until their divorce.<ref>{{cite news|title=\ud0e4\ub7f0\ud2b8 \uc774\ud61c\uc601 \u524d\ub0a8\ud3b8 \uc0ac\uae30 \uace0\uc18c|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=001&aid=0001418183|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Yonhap News|publisher=Naver|date=September 22, 2006|language=Korean}}</ref> In the suit, Lee Hye-young claimed that her ex-husband bought a Volvo worth 80 million won and a BMW worth 100 million won under her name, for which he did not repay the installment debt and caused money to be seized from her broadcasting payment and bank account. In the suit, Lee also claimed that her ex-husband forced her to pose as a\nnude model for business purposes, taking 50 million won (~$50,000) for the contract and 30 million won (~$30,000) worth of benefits from the\nproject.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kim|first1=Won-kyum|title=\uc774\ud61c\uc601, \uc804\ub0a8\ud3b8 \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \"\uc0ac\uae30\" \uace0\uc18c|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2006092206485451077&outlink=1&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.naver.com|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Star News|date=August 22, 2006|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kim|first1=Sang-ki|title=\ud0e4\ub7f0\ud2b8 \uc774\ud61c\uc601 \"\ubaa8\ubc14\uc77c \ud654\ubcf4 \uc774\uc775\uae08 \ub0b4\ub194\"\uc804 \ub0a8\ud3b8 \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \uace0\uc18c|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=143&aid=0000039519|accessdate=April 10, 2018|work=Kuki News|publisher=Naver|date=September 22, 2006|language=Korean}}</ref> On November 28, 2006, Lee Hye-young dropped the charges against her ex-husband.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kim|first1=Won-kyum|title=\uc774\ud61c\uc601, \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \uc0ac\uae30\ud610\uc758 \uace0\uc18c \ucde8\ud558|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2006112809562326517&outlink=1&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.naver.com|accessdate=April 15, 2018|work=Star News|date=November 28, 2006|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2006, the police arrested Lee on the suspicion of operating a gambling website and receiving 210 million won in proceeds.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uac00\uc218 \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \ub3c4\ubc15\uc0ac\uc774\ud2b8 \uc6b4\uc601 \ud610\uc758 \uc785\uac74|url=http://news.khan.co.kr/kh_news/khan_art_view.html?artid=200612111411031&code=940202|accessdate=April 15, 2018|work=Kyunghyang Shinmun|date=December 11, 2006|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sung|first1=So-young|title=Entertainer gambles with his career|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2926077|accessdate=April 15, 2018|work=Korea JoongAng Daily|date=September 16, 2010}}</ref> In 2009, he was sentenced to one and a half years in prison.<ref name=\"debut\">{{cite news|last=Choi|first=Jieun|title=\"Icon of Debt\": S Korea's Most Sought-After Celebrity|url=https://www.koreaexpose.com/icon-debt-koreas-sought-celebrity/|accessdate=April 15, 2018|work=Korea Expose|date=May 16, 2017}}</ref> However, Lee appealed the ruling, and was then sentenced to 3 years in probation, 160 hours in community service, and 210 million won in fines.<ref>{{cite news |title='\ub3c4\ubc15\uac1c\uc7a5' \ub8f0\ub77c \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc \ud56d\uc18c\uc2ec\uc11c \uc9d1\uc720 |url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=001&aid=0003273941 |accessdate=June 4, 2018 |work=Yonhap News |publisher=Naver News |date=May 13, 2010 |language=ko}}</ref>\n\nLee started a mega-restaurant featuring live martial arts battles and drag shows; however, the restaurant failed in 2005 and landed Lee in debts of 6.9 billion [[South Korean won|won]] ({{USD|6,200,000}}).<ref name=\"debut\" />\n\n== Discography ==\n* \"Blues Along the Way\" (2018)\n\n==Filmography==\n===TV series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Show !! Network !! Role !!class=\"unsortable| Notes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Confession Couple]]''\n| KBS2\n| Cameo\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Variety shows===\n\n====Current====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Show<ref name=\"sangmin show\">http://100.daum.net/encyclopedia/view/33XXXXX19500#tv</ref> !! Network !! class=\"unsortable| Notes\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n| ''[[Knowing Bros]]''\n| JTBC\n| Member of the permanent [[ensemble cast]] (episode 14{{ndash}}present)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\u2013present\n| ''[[Mom's Diary - My Ugly Duckling]]''\n| SBS\n| Permanent cast member starting from episode 32\n|-\n| ''{{ill|Section TV|ko|\uc139\uc158TV \uc5f0\uc608\ud1b5\uc2e0}}''\n| MBC\n| Main MC\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''A Man Running a Chart''\n| KBS Joy\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 2019\n| ''Interference with the shop 2''\n| KBS Joy\n|\n|-\n| ''Where is My Home?''\n| MBC\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Not the Same Person You Used to Know|Not the Same Person You Used to Know V2]]''\n| Mnet\n|\n|-\n| ''\ubc25\uce5c\uad6c''\n| sky Drama\n|\n|}\n\n====Previous====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Show<ref name=\"sangmin show\" /> !! Network !! class=\"unsortable| Notes\n|-\n| 2012 || ''{{ill|The God of Music|ko|\uc74c\uc545\uc758 \uc2e0}}'' || [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] || Member of an [[ensemble cast]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[The Genius: Rules of the Game]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" | [[TVN (South Korea)|tvN]] || Semi-finalist, 3rd place (eliminated in episode 11)\n|-\n| 2013{{ndash}}14 || ''[[The Genius: Rule Breaker]]'' || Show winner\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2014 || ''[[With You (South Korean TV series)|With You]]''\n| [[JTBC]] || Co-starred with [[Sayuri Fujita]]\n|-\n| ''{{ill|Share House (TV series)|lt=Share House|zh|Share house}}'' || [[O'live]] || Permanent cast\n|-\n| ''Entertainer Lives in My House'' || [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] || Episodes 1{{ndash}}2\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[The Genius: Grand Final]]'' || tvN || Finished in 11th place (eliminated in episode 3)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" | 2016 || ''[[The God of Music 2]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110410052 |title=\ube0c\ub85c\uc2a4 2\uae30 \uc628\ub2e4! \uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc+\u65b0\uba64\ubc84 \ucc3d\ub2e8\uc2dd['\uc74c\uc545\uc758\uc2e02'\u2460] |last=Dae Seon |first=Lee |date=May 17, 2016 |accessdate=March 1, 2017 |language=Korean |trans-title=The Brothers Are Here! Lee Sang Min and the New Members for The God of Music 2}}</ref>''\n|Mnet|| Member of an ensemble cast\n|-\n| ''[[Law of the Jungle (TV series)|Law of the Jungle]]'' || [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] || Episodes 238{{ndash}}240\n|-\n| ''[[Battle Trip]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]|| Contestant with Kim Il-jung (episode 7)\n|-\n| ''[[Immortal Songs 2]]'' || Roo'ra Special (episode 263)\n|-\n| ''[[King of Mask Singer]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |MBC|| Competed under the \"Rational Reason Apollo\" identity (episode 63)\n|-\n| ''Future Diary''\n|\n|-\n| ''Sing Street'' || Mnet || Permanent cast\n|-\n| ''[[Please Take Care of My Refrigerator]]'' || JTBC || Chef (Episodes 86{{ndash}}87)\n|-\n| ''Rumor Has It'' || Channel A || MC\n|-\n| 2016{{ndash}}17 || ''[[Singing Battle]]'' || KBS2 || Team leader\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2017\n| ''[[King of Mask Singer]]''\n|MBC|| Episodes 107{{ndash}}108 (as a panel member)\n|-\n| ''[[I Can See Your Voice#Season 2-5|I Can See Your Voice Seasons 2-5]]'' || Mnet || known as the \"God of Music\"\n|-\n| ''[[Oppa Thinking]]'' || MBC || Permanent cast (leader for the Team 2)\n|-\n| ''[[Heart Signal]]''\n| Channel A\n| Cast member\n|-\n| ''[[Fantastic Duo]] Season 2''\n| SBS\n| Guest starred with ''[[Roo'ra]]''\n|-\n| ''The Bunker 8''\n| XtM\n| Host\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\u201318\n| ''{{ill|It's Okay To Go A Little Crazy|ko|\uc0b4\uc9dd \ubbf8\uccd0\ub3c4 \uc88b\uc544}}''\n| SBS\n| Host\n|-\n| ''[[Where Is Mr. Kim]] Season 1-2''\n| tvN\n| Cast member since season 1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" |2018\n| ''[[The Call (South Korean TV series)|The Call]]''\n| Mnet\n| Co-host with ''[[Yoo Se-yoon]]''\n|-\n| ''[[One Night Sleepover Trip]]''\n| KBS\n| Permanent cast\n|-\n| ''[[Reckless but Happy]]''\n| SBS\n| Cast member<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://star.mk.co.kr/new/view.php?mc=ST&year=2018&no=579944|title=['\ubb34\ud655\ud589'\uccab\ubc29] \"\uc774\ud63c 13\ub144, \ud63c\ubc25 \uc775\uc219\"...\uc774\uc0c1\ubbfc, '\ub9db\uc694\uc815' \ub41c \uc774\uc720|work=mk.co.kr|access-date=2018-09-17|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''In A Moment - Lee Restaurant''\n| Comedy TV\n| Cast member\n|-\n| ''I Have Something To Say Today''\n| MBC every1\n|\n|-\n| ''Gourmet Road Season 4''\n| K-STAR\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Weekly Idol]]''\n| MBC Every1\n| Host\n|-\n| ''Lunch Time''\n| MBC\n| Cast member<ref>{{cite web |title=MC \uc18c\uac1c {{!}} \uad6c\ub0b4\uc2dd\ub2f9 |url=http://www.imbc.com/broad/tv/ent/cafeteria/mc/index.html |website=www.imbc.com |accessdate=16 August 2018 |language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018-19\n| ''The Fan''\n| SBS\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2019\n| ''[[Sky Castle]] Special''\n| JTBC\n| Host\n|-\n| ''\uc0bc\uac70\ub9ac \ub9cc\ud654\ubc29''\n| VIVO TV\n|\n|-\n| ''Interference with the shop Season 1''\n| KBS Joy\n|\n|-\n| ''\uc6d0\ud53d\ub85c\ub4dc''\n| Olive\n|\n|-\n| ''\uc9c0\uad6c\uc778 \ub77c\uc774\ube0c''\n| Channel A\n|\n|-\n| ''\