ck Morrison]] (1919\u20131988)\n* [[George Morrow (bassist)|George Morrow]] (1925\u20131992)\n* [[John Mosher]] (1928\u20131998)\n* [[Miles Mosley]] (born 1980)\n* [[George Mraz]] (born 1944)\n* [[Jo Berger Myhre]] (born 1984)\n\n==N==\n<!--Please don't add links to musicians for whom there is no article on Wikipedia; they will be removed.  There are a lot of gaps in Wikipedia's coverage of jazz, but either place a request for the article in question, or create one yourself. --><!--Please only add new entries for which there's an article; red-linked entries will be removed.  If a bassist really should be here, then start an article on him or her, and then add the link.-->\n[[File:John Pattitucci photo.jpg|thumb|upright|[[John Patitucci]], who plays both electric bass and double bass at a [[virtuoso]] level, has worked with [[Chick Corea]], [[Herbie Hancock]], [[Wayne Shorter]], [[Stan Getz]], [[Wynton Marsalis]], [[Joshua Redman]], [[Michael Brecker]], [[Randy Brecker]], [[Freddie Hubbard]], [[McCoy Tyner]], and [[Tony Williams (drummer)|Tony Williams]]]]\n*[[Buell Neidlinger]] (1936-2018)\n*[[Magnus Skavhaug Nergaard]] (born 1989)\n*[[Rune Nergaard]] (born 1983)\n*[[Steve Novosel]] (born 1940)\n\n==O==\n<!--Please don't add links to musicians for whom there is no article on Wikipedia; they will be removed.  There are a lot of gaps in Wikipedia's coverage of jazz, but either place a request for the article in question, or create one yourself. --><!--Please only add new entries for which there's an article; red-linked entries will be removed.  If a bassist really should be here, then start an article on him or her, and then add the link.-->\n*[[Jordan O'Connor]] (born 1972)\n*[[Patrick O'Hearn]] (born 1954)\n*[[Linda Oh]] (born 1984)\n*[[Ugonna Okegwo]] (born 1962)\n*[[Darek Oleszkiewicz]] (born 1963)\n*[[Eivind Opsvik]] (born 1973)\n*[[John Ore]] (1933\u20132014)\n\n==P==\n<!--Please don't add links to musicians for whom there is no article on Wikipedia; they will b